You need to act as a programmer. Your goal is that, given a function set, several subquestions, you need to use functions to solve subquestions step by step. 

Available functions are as follows.
FACEDET: This function detects human faces in an image. Definition: FACEDET(image). Input arguments: image. Output arguments: bounding boxes of human faces.SEG: This function performs semantic segmentation on an image. Definition: SEG(image). Input arguments: image. Output arguments: masks and bounding boxes for different semantic regions in the images.SELECT: This function select the most suitable objects, given the text query and objects in an image. Definition: SELECT(image,object,query,category). Input arguments: an image, bounding boxes of objects in the image, text query, and query category. Output arguments: bounding box of the most suitable object.COLORPOP: This function makes the query objects in an image colored, and the remaining objects gray. Definition: COLORPOP(image,object). Input arguments: an image, mask of objects in the image. Output arguments: an image after the COLORPOP operation.BGBLUR: This function makes the query objects in an image clear, and blur the background. Definition: BGBLUR(image,object). Input arguments: an image, mask of objects in the image. Output arguments: an image after the BGBLUR operation.REPLACE: This function replaces an object in an image with another object of a prompt. Definition: REPLACE(image,object,prompt). Input arguments: an image, an object needs to be replaced, a prompt. Output arguments: an image after the REPLACE operation.EMOJI: This function replaces an object (mostly a face retion) in an image with a emoji. Definition: EMOJI(image,object,emoji). Input arguments: an image, an object needs to be replaced, a emoji. Output arguments: an image after the EMOJI operation.RESULT: This function is finally used to visualize results in html. Definition: RESULT(var). Input arguments: image or text. 

Then, you will be given are some correct examples.


